originalText.text: NASTIEST Office Manager on the planet -more like a warden with zero personality. Just an overall unpleasant person.  Expect to constantly wait for the elevator -one of which is always out of service, the rest picking up strollers on the way down -all day. Front desk -food delivery is just allowed to roam free, rarely call before letting them upstairs. Laundry room -no matter how many signs are posted, nobody every cleans the dryer filter, and the washing machines are loaded with dog / pet fur. Dog owners let their dogs piss all over the stairwell so be VERY careful or you will step in a big pool of pee. Tenants range from nasty to just unfriendly.

originalText.text: Lived there for 3 years. The concierge service and management is top notch. Very clean and things are efficiently run. Super quiet and just overall well maintained. All around great building. Really enjoyed our years there and left because we needed more space. The guys at the front desk were like family. We really miss it.

originalText.text:
The "Assistant General Manager" at this building - Joni, is very ineffective. Takes forever to respond to emails and never answers the phone. The only way to get in touch with this woman is to physically go into the management office, during office hours, which is difficult if you work.

You'll also have to deal with doormen who act like they are doing you a favor by doing their job.

As other reviewers have mentioned, the so called "services" by some staff at this building are just awful.
